>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Chess — Board Game Terms That Score Big","description":"Chess words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. CHECKMATE (21pts), KNIGHT (14pts), BISHOP (13pts), PAWN (9pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-chess"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is CHECKMATE a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! CHECKMATE scores 21 points (C=3, H=4, E=1, C=3, K=5, M=3, A=1, T=1, E=1) as a 9-letter word. It means the winning position in chess. However, it's long and needs specific letters — shorter chess words may be more practical."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many points is KNIGHT worth in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"KNIGHT scores 14 points (K=5, N=1, I=1, G=2, H=4, T=1). It's the chess piece that moves in an L-shape. The K and H tiles together contribute 9 of the 14 points."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is GAMBIT valid in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. GAMBIT scores 11 points (G=2, A=1, M=3, B=3, I=1, T=1) and means an opening sacrifice in chess. It's a useful word when holding G, M, and B together — three mid-value consonants that can be tricky to place."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Chess — Board Game Terms That Score Big</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Chess and Scrabble are both strategy board games — and chess vocabulary translates beautifully to the tile rack. Piece names, tactical terms, and game states all contain high-value letters. KNIGHT uses both K and H, BISHOP stacks B and H together, and GAMBIT clears three mid-value consonants at once.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">21 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">CHECKMATE</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">14 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">KNIGHT</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">13 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">BISHOP</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">9 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">PAWN</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Chess Piece Names in Scrabble</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">KNIGHT — 14 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">K=5, N=1, I=1, G=2, H=4, T=1 · 6 letters · K+H combo</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">The only chess piece that can jump over others. KNIGHT combines K (5pts) and H (4pts) — two consonants that often strand players. At 14 points from 6 letters, it's the highest-scoring chess piece name you can play.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">♝ BISHOP</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">13 pts · B=3, I=1, S=1, H=4, O=1, P=3 · Diagonal mover</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">♚ KING</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">9 pts · K=5, I=1, N=1, G=2 · Most important piece</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">♛ QUEEN</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">14 pts · Q=10, U=1, E=1, E=1, N=1 · Most powerful piece</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">♟ PAWN</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">9 pts · P=3, A=1, W=4, N=1 · Front-line soldier</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Chess Tactics as Scrabble Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">GAMBIT</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CASTLE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CHECK</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">16pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">MATE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FORK</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">STALEMATE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Chess Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">QUEEN dumps the Q naturally:</span> At 14 points, QUEEN uses the Q (10pts) with two E tiles and common letters. It's one of the most intuitive Q words — every player has heard of it, so it's easy to remember under clock pressure.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">CHECK scores 16 from 5 tiles:</span> C=3, H=4, E=1, C=3, K=5. That's 3.2 points per tile — outstanding efficiency. It requires two C tiles, which isn't rare since there are 2 in the bag.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">KNIGHT for K+H racks:</span> Drawing K and H together feels like a penalty — until you remember KNIGHT. At 14 points it makes those two awkward tiles work together beautifully with common fillers (N, I, G, T).</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Chess words are <span class="text-white font-medium">multi-consonant solvers</span>. KNIGHT (K+H), BISHOP (B+H+P), CHECK (C+C+K), and GAMBIT (G+M+B) all clear multiple mid-value consonants in a single play. If your rack is loaded with 2-5 point consonants, think chess.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-games/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Games</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/best-q-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best Q Words for Scrabble</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-with-k/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words with K</span></a>
